Here is the commit message:
Modify SpEL code gen to take account of null safe refs

With this change the code generation for method and property
references is modified to include branching logic in the
case of null safe dereferencing (?.). This is complicated
by the possible usage of primitives on the left hand side
of the dereference. To cope with this case primitives are
promoted to boxed types when this situation occurs enabling
null to be passed as a possible result.

Issue: SPR-16489

Here is the root cause:
The bug arises from the inability of the SpEL code generation to properly handle null-safe dereferencing (using `?.`) when the left-hand side of the dereference involves primitive types. This leads to potential null pointer exceptions or incorrect behavior when attempting to access properties or methods on null objects, as primitives cannot represent null values. The modifications ensure that primitives are promoted to their boxed types, allowing null to be a valid result in such cases.

